odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

odd Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
odd Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
odd Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
odd Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Internal Data format:
Even Addresses: Bits [3:0]: antenna carrier index, 0-15 used for address generation for circuit switched types (unused for packet switched types)
Even Addresses: Bits [1:0]: Fifo index (used for packet switched type), 0-3 used to direct message to one of four FIFOs.
Even Addresses: 1'b1 causes circuit switched type to also capture to Error FIFO (fifo index 0x3)
Even Addresses: Illegal Address 1'b1: address is indicated to be illegal. Error condition is triggered.

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.
Bits [4:0]: OBSAI type, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [12:0]: OBSAI address, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [1:0]: Aggregation control bits (assuming Tx_Rule passes)

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.
Bits [4:0]: OBSAI type, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [12:0]: OBSAI address, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [1:0]: Aggregation control bits (assuming Tx_Rule passes)

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.
Bits [4:0]: OBSAI type, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [12:0]: OBSAI address, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [1:0]: Aggregation control bits (assuming Tx_Rule passes)

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.
Bits [4:0]: OBSAI type, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [12:0]: OBSAI address, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [1:0]: Aggregation control bits (assuming Tx_Rule passes)

UL RSA Format(only legal for burst of 8)

bitfield.description: Bits [2:0]: Circularly offsets reads from circuit switched RAM by n*4 chips. 8 chip orientated UL data disregard the LSB assuming it is zero. This offset is used to correct RAM alignment between streams different MOD32 offsets with one another. Allows chained DMA's to be more regular.
Bite [4:0]: pktsw FIFO Index[4:0]. Used to address fifo corresponding to this link.
Bits [4:0]: OBSAI type, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [12:0]: OBSAI address, fixed per antenna carrier (circuit switched only)
Bits [1:0]: Aggregation control bits (assuming Tx_Rule passes)

bitenum.description: NOP (Ag still pulls from FIFO, but does not use read PE data bytes)

Controls the data source selected by aggregator when there is an OBSAI header mismatch and the PE is requesting aggregation
Aggregator error checking enable: 0 = aggregator error checking disabled, 1 = aggregator error checking enabled.
Select aggregator mode: 00 = Not enabled (no data sent to the TX MAC), 01 = Pass thru from Combiner only, 10 = Insertion from the Protocol Encoder only, 11 = All aggregation functions enabled.
Summation overflow per AxC.

bitfield.description: CPRI data format:
Defines the measurement window for received Master Frame Offset, given in the number of vbus_clk tics.
Defines the measurement window for valid Master Frame Offset, given in the number of vbus_clk tics. Related to the error: mstr_frame_bndry_out_of_range.
Suppress error reporting of "extra" K28.7 characters detected in the data stream. RP3 requires that "messages be rejected when Master Frame boundary is detected outside the allowed window".

bitenum.description: Allow error reporting of extra K28.7 characters
Suppress error reporting of extra K28.7 characters

bitfield.description: Suppress error reporting when the receiver state machine is not in state ST3.
Force receiver state machine state: 0xx - not active, 100 - force ST0 state, 101 - force ST1 state, 110 - force ST2, 111 - force ST3 state.
Enable '1' or disable '0' RX MAC.

register.description: Rx MAC Link Pi Offset Configuration Register

bitfield.description: A 2's compliment number specifying the delay from Frame Sync to the expected Master Frame / Hyper Frame boundary (OBSAI RP3: K28.7 or CPRI: K28.5 AND HFN = 149) within ~65 ns (about 5, 1x link byte clocks) and given in the number of vbus_clk tics.

register.description: Rx MAC Link LoS Threshold Configuration Register

bitfield.description: Sets 8b10b los detect threshold values in number of Line Code Violations received. Writing to this location will automatically clear the rm_num_los counter and rm_los_det status bit.

register.description: RX MAC Link Status Register A

bitfield.description: This error is indicated when received Master Frame is detected outside the programmable window valid_mstr_frame_wind. This error will not be reported if an "extra" K28.7 character is detected AND rm_extra_k28p7_err_suppress = 1.
Detectes when rm_num_los counter has reached the programmable rm_los_det_thold limit.
Active when rx state machine is in ST0 state, inactive otherwise.
Indicates the current status of the rx state machine. ST0 = '1000', ST1 = '0100', ST2 = '0010', ST3 = '0001'

register.description: RX MAC Link Status Register B

bitfield.description: Reperesents the time in vbus_clk tics from after pi_offset that the frame boundary was received. This value will saturate at either the programmed rm_rcvd_mstr_frame_wind threshold or the max value of 4095. This measurement is conducted once per frame.

This error is indicated when received Master Frame is detected outside the programmable window valid_mstr_frame_wind. This error will not be reported if an "extra" K28.7 character is detected AND rm_extra_k28p7_err_suppress = 1.

register.description: RX MAC Link Status Register C

bitfield.description: Active high status indicates Loss Of Frame when the receiver FSM is in state ST0 or ST1.
Active high status indicates when the receiver FSM is in the HFSYNC state ST3.

Received Node B Frame number low byte (Z.128.0)
Received Hyperframe number (Z.64.0)
